## On-disk layout (host-internal ÔÇö plans/docs only)

Sedea binds operations **plans/docs** to one **workspace-bound scope segment** under `.sedea/operations/` (host-internal). Agents must **not** construct or document user-id path segments ÔÇö use **`dispatchId`**, **`operationsDocsDirectory`**, and explicit plan paths from spawn **`inputs`**.

| Subtree | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `plans/` | Flat plan union for this workspace scope |
| `docs/` | Scope-level operational docs |
| `dispatch/<epochMs>/` | **Abandoned legacy** filesystem bundles ÔÇö product must not depend on them |

Legacy installs may still have `user`, `joint`, or per-user UUID scope folders ÔÇö migrate with the customer script below.

