## Checkpoint step continuation (binding)

This file is the **dispatch-scope and DbOnly terminal operations-storage contract** (`dispatchId`, `operationsDocsDirectory`, docs write-root resolution, retired Hybrid / FsReadOnly) ÔÇö not a mission protocol with executable ship steps. Under **`trustLevel: checkpoint`**, applying host-supplied scope and writing under a resolved docs root **auto-advances**; missing binding fields return **`partial`** with `outputs.missingFields` (no turn-end modal owned by this rule). **Do not** add literal `USER_CHECKPOINT` gate markers here ÔÇö markers and option tables live on invoker skills and rule **2**.

| Surface | Designation | Owner |
|---------|-------------|--------|
| Apply host-supplied `dispatchId` / `operationsDocsDirectory` / slot id | **auto-advance** | ┬ž *Agent dispatch scope (binding)* |
| Docs write when Priority 1ÔÇô2 root resolves | **auto-advance** | ┬ž *Docs write root resolution* |
| Docs write when no root resolvable Ôćĺ `partial` + `missingFields` | **auto-advance** | ┬ž *Docs write root resolution* Priority 3 ÔÇö stop write; invoker may open a pick |
| Spawned skill missing dispatch scope fields Ôćĺ `partial` | **auto-advance** | ┬ž *Spawned skill outputs* ÔÇö invoker / Squad Leader recovery |
| `plan-state.mjs` / completeness cwd contract (reference) | **baseline-governs** (reference) | ┬ž *`plan-state.mjs` (canonical)* ÔÇö execution owned by invoker |
| Customer migration dry-run / execute documentation | **baseline-governs** (reference) | ┬ž *Customer migration* ÔÇö operator runbook; not lane turn UX |
| Forbidden path construction / mtime dispatch discovery | **baseline-governs** (reference) | ┬ž *Agent dispatch scope* Forbidden list ÔÇö policy only |

**Forbidden in this file:** prescribing prose *tell me when* / *come back when* / *I'll wait* / *over to you* / *reply with results* after a missing-scope or docs-root gap; prose-only exit that invents `dispatchId` or scans sibling dispatch folders; live `USER_CHECKPOINT` tokens on happy-path scope application.

**Related:** Checkpoint step-table template ÔÇö [`.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/pr-step-table-template.md`](.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/pr-step-table-template.md). Marker syntax ÔÇö [`.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/user-checkpoint-marker-syntax.md`](.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/user-checkpoint-marker-syntax.md). Turn completion ÔÇö [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc).

